text: .@jonkarl says Trump’s strategy “seems to be to basically create doubt about the integrity of the election itself, which seems to be reflection that he believes that if all the counting goes on to conclusion, he will not emerge in the lead.” https://t.co/6oJ9txzJZ1 #Election2020 https://t.co/SY7dMZbcgy

text: Cruise Lines International Association announced today that its members would maintain the ongoing voluntary suspension of cruise operations in the U.S. through Dec. 31, 2020. https://t.co/HwXvevv1mo

name: ABC
text: “It is mathematically possible” for Joe Biden to close the gap and win the state of Georgia, “though the math and the vote generally favors the president here,” ABC News’ @SteveOsunsami reports. https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 #2020Election https://t.co/dsxaUS8uGq

name: ABC
text: .@matthewjdowd on the state of #Election2020: “We’re as divided as we were since 1860...Abraham Lincoln won that election in 1860 with 40% of the vote.” https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 #Election2020 https://t.co/YEQEkB8rtk

name: ABC
text:
Voters in Mississippi approved the design of a new state flag, which will include an image of a magnolia, the state flower, and the phrase "In God We Trust."

The previous state flag featured the Confederate Battle Cross. https://t.co/4APQcacpJM

name: ABC
text: NEW: As votes are being counted, the Trump campaign filed a lawsuit in Georgia on Wednesday night — its third of the day. https://t.co/DDJAqVnyni #Election2020

name: ABC
text:
Firefighters in Honduras helped save several people, including an infant, from flooding caused by Tropical Storm Eta.

Although Eta has weakened to a tropical depression, it continues to bring life-threatening flooding to parts of Central America. https://t.co/IAO1tLMcYK https://t.co/jDxNLn2e3P

name: ABC
text: NEW: Incumbent Democratic Sen. Gary Peters wins Michigan Senate race, @ABC News projects. https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 #Election2020 https://t.co/StM4La0kth

name: ABC
text: GOP Rep. Adam Kinzinger on Trump's ballot claims: “If there is a legitimate concern and you have evidence of that, there’s an entire court system…set up to handle that. But it is not by making accusations through Twitter that have a reverberating impact” https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 https://t.co/sB3vRQNvW0

text:

name: ABC
text: .@devindwyer says Biden campaign “not worried at all” about legal threats because there isn't a convincing "constitutional argument put forward in any court by the Trump campaign that would challenge the legitimacy of any of the results in a real way.” https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 https://t.co/Z2Kg8qStp3

name: ABC
text: .@GStephanopoulos: "It has been more than 24 hours now since the first polls closed—and this race for the White House, which has drawn record number of Americans to cast their ballots, is creeping towards a conclusion." https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 #Election2020 https://t.co/btk5bfD1y0

name: ABC
text: .@DavidMuir: "It's been lost today in this...election night that continues into tonight: 100,000 new cases of COVID in just 24 hours in this country." https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 #Election2020 https://t.co/cWPEruIQD2

name: ABC
text: RT @ABCPolitics: .@NateSilver538 says the Trump campaign "has a reasonable argument" that they could catch Joe Biden's vote total in Arizona as ballots continue to be tabulated. https://t.co/DA8JdVxU42 #Election2020 https://t.co/T9oh5TVaeo

name: ABC
text: .@CeciliaVega says people close to President Trump say "he is in a down mood behind the scenes. He is starting to concede, at least to people around him, that he is seeing this lead slip away. People on his team are holding out hope for Arizona.” https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 https://t.co/GUjQ2xaMmE

name: ABC
text:
Pennsylvania Secretary of State Kathy Boockvar says they are “ahead of schedule,” with “under a million” ballots yet to be counted in Pennsylvania.

“I now believe that the overwhelming majority of ballots will be counted by tomorrow.” https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 #Election2020 https://t.co/RIw2OpYmfa

name: ABC
text:
RT @ABCPolitics: .@WhitJohnson updates on the race in Arizona, where "Joe Biden is still holding onto that lead, although it is a slight lead."

"Mark Kelly is actually outperforming Joe Biden—and there is that potential...where they split the ticket."
https://t.co/DA8JdVxU42 #Election2020 https://t.co/Xeo0QIyYLC

name: ABC
text:
“I don’t,” Pennsylvania Secretary of State Kathy Boockvar tells @GStephanopoulos when asked if legal action by the Trump campaign will make a difference.

“We want to make sure that no voter is disenfranchised .. so we’re going to count every vote.”  https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 https://t.co/D9nUXzuyAs

name: ABC
text: .@ChrisChristie on Pres. Trump: “He’s a fighter and he hasn’t given up yet”; says Trump camp is focused on AZ from a political perspective. https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 #Election2020 https://t.co/ZORcxUAYzp

name: ABC
text: Chris Christie on some predictions of a "blue wave" in 2020: "We didn't have any wave; we had an undertow." https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 #Election2020 https://t.co/LqC7qQBDhF

name: ABC
text: RT @ABCPolitics: .@danabrams to @GStephanopoulos’ question on if Trump camp’s legal challenges will make a difference in #Election2020: “Probably not.” https://t.co/DA8JdVxU42 #Election2020 https://t.co/W3vvOjpzSn

name: ABC
text:
Chris Christie says he thinks Pres. Trump "will fight to the end."

"At least in...the next couple of weeks, I don't think he'll just throw up his hands, say, 'All right, it's over'—unless some of the results become overwhelming." https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 #Election2020 https://t.co/9e70R73ePx

name: ABC
text: “Traditionally, the Justice Department has viewed vote counting as a state matter,” and so far, there’s “no indication” DOJ would seek to help the Trump campaign, @PierreTABC says, adding that experts say such an intervention “would be unprecedented.” https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 https://t.co/pUuHMUUcKA

name: ABC
text:
"History would suggest that America has always been divided, since 1619," @byronpitts says in comments reflecting on political polarization.

"Our history has always been complicated, it has always been muddy, it has always been difficult." https://t.co/GwwRl4EUb3 https://t.co/8oFSMT2Kru

text:
LATEST: Election officials in Arizona's Maricopa County say that they have an estimated 275,000 more ballots to process and tabulate.

text:
